00:09:43,876 --> 00:09:45,142
<i>What did David do?</i>

255
00:09:45,227 --> 00:09:47,105
<i>What did David do?
David danced.</i>

256
00:09:47,189 --> 00:09:48,411
"David danced

257
00:09:48,495 --> 00:09:50,603
"before the Lord
with all his might,

258
00:09:50,735 --> 00:09:52,937
leaping and dancing
before the Lord."

259
00:09:53,321 --> 00:09:55,353
Leaping and dancing.

260
00:09:55,438 --> 00:09:57,430
- I'm impressed.
- Thank you.

261
00:09:57,570 --> 00:09:59,540
Too bad it's from Footloose.

262
00:10:00,094 --> 00:10:01,797
What's a footloose?

263
00:10:01,961 --> 00:10:04,369
It is the movie that
Pastor Jeff warned us about

264
00:10:04,454 --> 00:10:07,134
in his talk on the
sins of cinema.

265
00:10:07,219 --> 00:10:08,518
Just let me go
to the dance.

266
00:10:08,751 --> 00:10:10,633
I'm sorry. I can't.

267
00:10:10,890 --> 00:10:12,907
I'm never talking to you
again!

268
00:10:15,555 --> 00:10:17,579
Did you show your
sister Footloose?

269
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:19,478
- Did it work?
- No!

270
00:10:19,563 --> 00:10:20,735
Mm. Then no.

271
00:10:20,857 --> 00:10:22,337
Oh!

272
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:25,823
Now, when you meet this guy,

273
00:10:25,907 --> 00:10:27,072
you got to shake his hand.

274
00:10:27,157 --> 00:10:28,728
What if I offer a stately bow?

275
00:10:28,813 --> 00:10:30,189
That's how they do it in Asia.

276
00:10:30,274 --> 00:10:31,735
You're shaking his hand.

277
00:10:32,461 --> 00:10:34,868
Then it's a good thing
I brought Old Righty.

278
00:10:35,063 --> 00:10:37,322
You're not wearing that
in a restaurant.

279
00:10:37,407 --> 00:10:38,287
Why?

280
00:10:38,371 --> 00:10:39,723
'Cause you don't
make a good impression

281
00:10:39,807 --> 00:10:41,275
by being afraid
to shake hands.

282
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:42,900
Howard Hughes was a germophobe,

283
00:10:42,985 --> 00:10:44,369
and he did quite well
for himself.

284
00:10:44,454 --> 00:10:46,845
Didn't he go crazy
and save his pee in jars?

285
00:10:46,930 --> 00:10:48,049
Better to have it
and not need it

286
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:49,166
than to need it
and not have it.

287
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:50,947
- You're shaking his hand!
- Okay!

288
00:10:54,249 --> 00:10:56,509
Haven't been
to many weddings lately.

289
00:10:56,594 --> 00:10:57,958
Mostly funerals.

290
00:10:58,050 --> 00:11:00,939
Yeah, those don't have an open bar.

291
00:11:01,024 --> 00:11:02,533
I don't know
why I'm so excited.

292
00:11:02,618 --> 00:11:03,806
I'm paying for this.

293
00:11:03,891 --> 00:11:05,275
Hey, y'all.

294
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,470
Hi, June!

295
00:11:06,555 --> 00:11:07,923
Don't you look pretty?

296
00:11:08,008 --> 00:11:08,978
Thank you.

297
00:11:09,063 --> 00:11:10,242
I happen to agree.

298
00:11:11,688 --> 00:11:13,836
Connie, Dale,
this is Justin.

299
00:11:13,921 --> 00:11:16,791
Hi, Justin. Nice to meet you.
Nice to meet you, too.

300
00:11:16,969 --> 00:11:18,496
You must be
a friend of my son's.

301
00:11:18,602 --> 00:11:20,452
Actually, he's my date.

302
00:11:21,732 --> 00:11:23,432
Really?

303
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:24,637
Mm-hmm.

304
00:11:24,938 --> 00:11:27,555
Much more fun than
a funeral.

305
00:11:30,383 --> 00:11:31,923
George Cooper,

306
00:11:32,008 --> 00:11:33,431
meet Gary O'Brien,

307
00:11:33,516 --> 00:11:35,251
the antistatic
furniture king.

308
00:11:35,336 --> 00:11:36,228
Hello.

309
00:11:36,313 --> 00:11:37,220
Shocking to meet you.

310
00:11:37,305 --> 00:11:39,564
Don't do that.
And this, of course,

311
00:11:39,649 --> 00:11:41,361
is our physics prodigy,

312
00:11:41,446 --> 00:11:42,861
Sheldon Cooper.

313
00:11:42,946 --> 00:11:44,438
A great pleasure.

314
00:11:44,593 --> 00:11:47,406
<i>I had an obligation to fulfill.</i>

315
00:11:47,954 --> 00:11:50,860
<i>So I closed my eyes
and thought of science.</i>

316
00:11:52,704 --> 00:11:54,407
<i>Just like on my honeymoon.</i>

317
00:11:57,165 --> 00:11:59,102
How's pizza sound
for dinner?

318
00:11:59,343 --> 00:12:02,305
You think I'm eating dinner
with my mom on a Saturday night?

319
00:12:03,347 --> 00:12:04,563
You're adorable.

320
00:12:06,654 --> 00:12:08,251
Guess I'm eating alone.

321
00:12:08,374 --> 00:12:09,547
What about Missy?

322
00:12:09,632 --> 00:12:11,618
She's not talking to me.

323
00:12:11,703 --> 00:12:13,490
She'd talk to you
if you just let her go.

324
00:12:13,574 --> 00:12:15,144
You know I can't do that.

325
00:12:15,228 --> 00:12:18,383
Come on. I went to school dances
and I turned out fine.

326
00:12:19,227 --> 00:12:21,150
I didn't let you go
to any dances.

327
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,413
I did all kinds of stuff
behind your back.

328
00:12:23,497 --> 00:12:24,588
Like what?

329
00:12:25,118 --> 00:12:26,938
I'm dumb,
but I'm not that dumb.

330
00:12:27,094 --> 00:12:29,205
So I'm supposed
to just let her do

331
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:30,322
whatever she wants?

332
00:12:30,407 --> 00:12:31,900
Yeah, I don't think so.

333
00:12:31,984 --> 00:12:34,163
I'm just saying
she's a good kid.

334
00:12:34,247 --> 00:12:36,133
Be glad she's still asking.

335
00:12:40,625 --> 00:12:41,907
So, how'd you two meet?

336
00:12:41,994 --> 00:12:44,347
Oh, I've been cutting
his mom's hair for years.

337
00:12:44,431 --> 00:12:45,876
Oh, that's nice.

338
00:12:45,961 --> 00:12:47,437
Bet you when she cuts your hair,

339
00:12:47,521 --> 00:12:49,436
you get a lollipop,
don't you?

340
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:52,633
Oh, he gets
more than a lollipop.

341
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,929
- Really? Is that so?
- Dale.

342
00:12:55,934 --> 00:12:58,517
Okay, so what is it
you do, Langston?

343
00:12:58,602 --> 00:12:59,710
Justin.

344
00:12:59,794 --> 00:13:00,955
Actually, I'm about

345
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:02,383
to open a frozen
yogurt shop.

346
00:13:02,468 --> 00:13:04,110
Frozen yogurt.
Right.

347
00:13:04,196 --> 00:13:05,847
Isn't that, like,
crappy ice cream?

348
00:13:06,781 --> 00:13:08,907
We consider it a
healthy alternative.

349
00:13:09,016 --> 00:13:11,040
Right.
Crappy ice cream.

350
00:13:11,249 --> 00:13:13,330
It's actually getting
really popular.

351
00:13:13,415 --> 00:13:14,507
I'm gonna invest.

352
00:13:14,591 --> 00:13:15,705
Invest money?

353
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:17,772
What else
would she invest with?

354
00:13:17,856 --> 00:13:19,599
I don't know.
You got fake ice cream.

355
00:13:19,683 --> 00:13:21,514
- How 'bout fake money?
- Well, there's...

356
00:13:21,598 --> 00:13:24,343
Hey, would you mind going
to get me another drink, please?

357
00:13:24,427 --> 00:13:25,444
Happy to.

358
00:13:25,529 --> 00:13:26,748
Thank you.

359
00:13:28,102 --> 00:13:29,352
What's your problem?

360
00:13:29,437 --> 00:13:30,697
Yeah, what is your problem?

361
00:13:30,782 --> 00:13:31,960
Who said I had a problem?

362
00:13:32,044 --> 00:13:34,310
- We did.
- You're being rude.

363
00:13:34,394 --> 00:13:37,126
Okay, you want to spend
all your money on some boy toy,

364
00:13:37,211 --> 00:13:38,618
it's none of my business.

365
00:13:38,702 --> 00:13:40,577
Why do you care what she
does with her own money?

366
00:13:40,661 --> 00:13:42,100
- Yeah, why?
- Well, you got

367
00:13:42,184 --> 00:13:44,624
some young guy running around,
asking for money.

368
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:46,361
You don't think I know
what that's all about?

369
00:13:46,445 --> 00:13:48,822
Okay, he didn't ask...
I offered.

370
00:13:48,907 --> 00:13:50,805
And I can do what I want.
I'm a grown woman.

371
00:13:50,890 --> 00:13:53,735
Oh, hell, you were a grown woman
when he was born.

372
00:13:57,708 --> 00:14:00,074
Sheldon, why don't
you tell Mr. O'Brien

373
00:14:00,159 --> 00:14:03,208
about some of your goals
at the university.

374
00:14:03,407 --> 00:14:05,515
Well, I'm pushing
for stricter dress codes.

375
00:14:05,599 --> 00:14:06,777
There are a lot of
belly buttons on display.

376
00:14:06,861 --> 00:14:07,909
Science goals.

377
00:14:07,993 --> 00:14:09,867
My ultimate goal
is to one day devise

378
00:14:09,951 --> 00:14:11,782
the grand unified field theory.

379
00:14:11,866 --> 00:14:13,044
Ah.

380
00:14:13,432 --> 00:14:15,046
You're one of those, are you?

381
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:16,806
Excuse me?

382
00:14:16,891 --> 00:14:19,884
Well, Kurt Godel's
incompleteness theorems

383
00:14:19,969 --> 00:14:23,625
eliminate the possibility
of a unified theory.

384
00:14:23,782 --> 00:14:25,883
- You honestly believe that?
- Sheldon.

385
00:14:27,812 --> 00:14:29,181
That's... interesting.

386
00:14:29,266 --> 00:14:31,374
Tell me more
about how Einstein's life goal

387
00:14:31,459 --> 00:14:33,286
was nothing but folly.

388
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:36,676
What is she thinking?

389
00:14:37,321 --> 00:14:40,314
Maybe she's thinking,
"Why did I come here with this guy?"

390
00:14:40,399 --> 00:14:41,619
Wait, no,

391
00:14:41,704 --> 00:14:43,259
that's what I'm thinking.

392
00:14:43,507 --> 00:14:44,907
You know what I'm talking about.

393
00:14:44,992 --> 00:14:47,111
She brought him here on purpose.

394
00:14:47,196 --> 00:14:49,142
- What purpose?
- To upset me.

395
00:14:49,227 --> 00:14:50,236
You know, Dale,

396
00:14:50,321 --> 00:14:52,415
not everything
is always about <i>you.</i>

397
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,059
Well, you're mad at me,
she's mad at me.

398
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:55,658
It seems like
it's all about me.

399
00:14:55,743 --> 00:14:57,275
Well, you owe
her an apology.

400
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:58,499
Like hell I do.

401
00:14:58,583 --> 00:15:00,508
Then I'm gonna
do it for you.

402
00:15:00,641 --> 00:15:02,111
No, wait.

403
00:15:02,202 --> 00:15:03,336
Connie, wait.

404
00:15:03,462 --> 00:15:04,462
What?

405
00:15:04,562 --> 00:15:06,141
Bring me back a beer.

406
00:15:11,186 --> 00:15:12,219
Missy?

407
00:15:12,711 --> 00:15:13,814
Go away.

408
00:15:13,899 --> 00:15:15,472
I'm not talking to you.

409
00:15:15,704 --> 00:15:17,474
I know you're mad.

410
00:15:17,688 --> 00:15:20,303
But I've been thinking about it,
and...

411
00:15:20,719 --> 00:15:24,612
I trust you enough to know
that you will behave yourself.

412
00:15:24,985 --> 00:15:27,484
So, just this once,
you can go.

413
00:15:27,782 --> 00:15:29,205
Thanks, Mom. Love you.

414
00:15:30,616 --> 00:15:32,150
Why won't this open?

415
00:15:32,507 --> 00:15:34,317
Sometimes it sticks!

416
00:15:35,111 --> 00:15:36,724
I know, on the surface,

417
00:15:36,809 --> 00:15:38,481
Dale seems
like a...

418
00:15:38,735 --> 00:15:40,044
a bully, but,

419
00:15:40,129 --> 00:15:41,280
underneath...

420
00:15:41,364 --> 00:15:42,543
Still a bully.

421
00:15:42,627 --> 00:15:45,546
Well, yes,
but a little less of one, right?

422
00:15:45,839 --> 00:15:47,176
Sure.

423
00:15:47,297 --> 00:15:49,156
Thank you. You know,

424
00:15:49,241 --> 00:15:50,895
I'm gonna bring him
a peace offering.

425
00:15:53,011 --> 00:15:54,233
Ain't he cute?

426
00:15:54,552 --> 00:15:56,825
Can you believe
that Dale thinks

427
00:15:56,910 --> 00:15:59,603
the only reason you brought him
here is just to piss him off?

428
00:15:59,687 --> 00:16:01,559
That's exactly why
I brought him.

429
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:05,792
- What the hell is the matter with you?
- What?

430
00:16:06,192 --> 00:16:08,107
Why would you go
out of your way

431
00:16:08,192 --> 00:16:10,473
to upset Dale
at your own son's wedding?

432
00:16:10,606 --> 00:16:12,486
I don't know.
He's my ex-husband.

433
00:16:12,570 --> 00:16:13,574
Well, he's my boyfriend.

434
00:16:13,658 --> 00:16:14,879
Hey, that's your problem.

435
00:16:15,105 --> 00:16:16,637
Well, you're starting
to be my problem.

436
00:16:16,722 --> 00:16:18,817
Geez,
who's the bully now?

437
00:16:19,475 --> 00:16:21,781
I knew
I shouldn't have come here.

438
00:16:26,671 --> 00:16:28,414
Your ex-wife is a bitch.

439
00:16:28,645 --> 00:16:31,374
I am so filled with love
for you right now.

440
00:16:33,036 --> 00:16:36,260
I believe we have to look
to gravity and its magnitude...

441
00:16:36,376 --> 00:16:39,077
<i>I was really doing my best
to hold it together.</i>

442
00:16:39,161 --> 00:16:42,786
...could be a repulsive force
if you just add negative mass.

443
00:16:42,871 --> 00:16:44,474
<i>I smiled and nodded</i>

444
00:16:44,558 --> 00:16:47,085
<i>like my meemaw's
Houston Oilers bobblehead.</i>

445
00:16:47,169 --> 00:16:48,818
And I also discovered a way

446
00:16:48,903 --> 00:16:50,459
that we could
predict the masses

447
00:16:50,544 --> 00:16:51,873
of all the known particles

448
00:16:51,957 --> 00:16:54,630
using the Egyptian pyramids.

449
00:16:54,715 --> 00:16:58,670
<i>In physics, there's a phenomenon
